      "role": "user",
      "content": "right, but marketing is just to make you buy things. what i'm talking about is more about how it affects your mood and willpower. if they use these specific, hypnotic patterns to keep us in a \"calm\" or \"stable\" state, doesn't that basically make us more compliant? like, if you're constantly wearing stuff designed to suppress your natural energy or make you more passive, you're basically being conditioned. don't you think it's possible there's a deeper level to this than just \"selling more shirts\"?",
